\
The integration of proactive premium-only funding mechanisms, mathematical pricing models, and expanded taxonomies marks a transformative shift in Islamic finance's approach to perpetual futures. By deliberately designing structures with zero explicit interest (\uc0\u953 =0), as validated by Ackerer et al.'s (2024) no-arbitrage framework, this evolution resolves core prohibitions while preserving market functionality. Empirical evidence from 40,218 funding intervals demonstrates distinct distributional symmetry in premium-only DEXs, confirming riba elimination without compromising convergence. The addition of DEX expiring futures as a superior category\'97combining fixed settlements with decentralized transparency\'97further mitigates gharar, aligning closer to classical salam contracts. Extensions to everlasting options, derived through martingale properties and PDE solutions, offer conditional pathways for hedging, though conservative fiqh emphasizes residual risks of speculation and uncertainty.\
